{
  "name": "RPlog_Honor_Among_Killers",
  "title": "The Skin of Samus",
  "summary": "At the Imperial Embassy, the hunter Taggor seeks out the scarred Ambassador Morganna to ask what she knows of the bounty hunter Detjin and whether he would have reason to join the Hunters' Guild. Their conversation turns grim when Morganna boasts of a trophy in her collection, the skin of a Horansi named Samus, who turns out to have been Taggor's dear friend and master. After an angry confrontation, Morganna explains that Detjin, not she, killed the feline, and that she merely purchased the skin. Moved by Taggor's grief, she leads him to her private trophy chamber and, in an unexpected gesture of honor between killers, permits him to perform Horansi death rites over Samus and take the pelt away to lay it to rest properly. Taggor accepts, promising to replace it with the next Horansi he hunts, and the two part on uneasy but mutually respectful terms, with Morganna warning him to keep her involvement secret from a figure named Sharkad.",
